{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, we were able to cut the computational time for inference in AbstRCT by 30% without sacrificing performance by stopping the model from producing irrelevant text spans, which are not arguments.",
    "Finding the arguments in a text, defining the type of argument, and establishing the relationships between the arguments are the three crucial subtasks that comprise AM.",
    "These actions are essential for exposing a text's argumentation structure.",
    "Previous approaches employed a pipeline architecture, with relation classifications and component classification1 coming after argumentative span identification (Persing and Ng, 2016; Eger et al., 2017; Kuribayashi et al., 2019; Morio et al., 2020).",
    "Nevertheless, this method may lead to the accumulation of mistakes from earlier subtasks."
  ]
}